Head broader than long (0.5 × 
0.9 mm
), dark brown-black, markedly darker than pronotum, around the base of antennae brighter; shiny, coarsely punctuated, with long yellowish setae. Clypeus and labrum brown with long yellowish setae. Mandibles brown-black; maxillary palpi consist of three brown segments with short brown, erect setae. Eyes distinct, exceeding the head margins, with sparse, short and lightly colored setae. There is a small de- pression between the eyes.

Pronotum is broader (
1 mm
) than long (
1.25 mm
) (ratio 0.8: 1.0), brown, shiny, coarsely and densely punctate, with long yellowish protruding setae of similar length as those on elytra. Posterior corners of the pronotum obtuse. Pronotum rounded on the sides, broadest part at 3/5 at its length. Base of the pronotum marginate, bulged at the middle and strongly extending beyond posterior corners of pronotum. The bulged part covers about half of the basis width. Transition between the narrow and bulged part is sudden. There are two marginal circular imprints near the pronotal base (close to the posterior corners).

Elytra oval-shaped, 1.9 times longer (
3.2 mm
) than broad (
1.7 mm
) (ratio 1.9: 1.0), shiny, bearing long, dense, erect yellowish setae. The broadest part is at the middle of the elytral length Punctation dense and coarse. Elytra are dark brown with seven light patches. Large irregular patch is at 2/5 of elytral length in the direction from base. Small patch on the humeri, on apex of elytra and four small patches are situated at 3/5 of elytra, where they form irregular and interrupted strip. Elytral apex round. Ventral side brown, ventrites bearing long yellowish setae. Legs brown with erect yellowish setae with the exception of median and hind tibiae that bear shorter, darker setae (dark brown) than rest of legs. Setae on legs shorter than those on elytra. All tibiae possess two brown apical spurs.
